Based on the search results, I found information about how the Dune movies have generated significant meme culture and reactions among Gen Z and youth audiences on TikTok. Here's what I discovered:

## TikTok Memes and Youth Reactions to Dune

The internet has turned the Dune movies into a "meme factory," with the worldwide web being "ablaze with any and all wisecracks" about the films. The movie has been "one of the year's most eagerly anticipated movies" and "the internet is having fun with it".

### The "Silence!" Meme Phenomenon

One of the most popular TikTok trends related to Dune features people yelling "silence" as loud as possible in public spaces while being recorded, mimicking a scene from Dune: Part 2 said by Timothée Chalamet. The trend was popularized on TikTok in March 2024, with TikToker @luvsickdracko notably starting it.

The original videos showed someone standing on a lunch table at school yelling "silence!" referencing the Dune Part 2 scene, garnering over 9.6 million and 7 million views in just four days. The videos feature captions like "Bro might be Paul Atreides", showing how Gen Z has embraced the character.

### Youth Reactions to Timothée Chalamet

The search results show enthusiastic reactions from young fans, with comments like "amazing. spectacular. would die for timothée chalamet" appearing in social media responses to the film.

### Broader Meme Culture

Fans have been having fun with Dune's desert visuals by "deliberately confusing it with other desert-set pop culture landmarks" and creating various memes. There's "everything from red carpet jokes to sandworm shuffles" in the meme landscape surrounding the films.

The search results demonstrate how Gen Z has embraced both Dune films through creative meme-making, viral TikTok trends, and enthusiastic reactions to Timothée Chalamet's portrayal of Paul Atreides, turning the epic sci-fi franchise into a significant part of youth culture on social media platforms.
